### Steps to reproduce
- open a terminal
- type the command: `git clone https://github.com/crisz/example-vue-ts-app.git`
- install dependencies: `npm install`
- run the script: `npm run dev:build`
- open the **build/index.html** file

### What is expected?
The "Hello World" application to appear

### What is actually happening?
The page is blank and there is the following error in the console:
Failed to mount component: template or render function not defined


---
What I did was just copying the src folder from the @vue/cli ts default "Hello World" application to try to build it on my own with webpack, but after a lot of attempts and days spent, nothing seems working.
 
